notes.text:
Transcribed notes from Christiana Carlile obituary Wasatch Wave, "Local Waves" December 1, 1891

The Oldest Resident of Heber has Passed Away.

Mrs. Christiana Carlile died yesterday morning at the resident of her son George Carlile in this city.   She has for a long time had the distinction of being the oldest person in Wasatch county, being nearly ninety-five years old.

The deceased was born in England on the first day of February, 1797.  She was the daughter of James and Nance Sponnser.  With her family she joined the church of Jesus Christ of Ltter-Day Saints in 1848 and the following year they started for Utah, arriving at New Orleans Christmas eve, 1849.   She came to Utah in 1852 and settled at Spanish Fork, but in 1860 she moved to this valley where she has since lived.   Mrs. Carlile was the mother of seven children, four of who are still living, one in England, one in Iowa, and two here.  She has twenty-two grand children, fifty-three great-grandchildren and four great-great grandchildren now living in Utah.   The posterity of her other two children is not known.  She died as she has lived, a faithful Latter-Day Saint.

The funeral takes place this afternoon t the Stake House at 2 o'clock.
